ine 145:     \"causal_summary\": \"deep-loop-workflows is the single public skill that merges active deep-loop persona modes (deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, deep-improvement) into one advisor identity with active mode packets, routed by workflowMode through mode-registry.json over the frozen MCP-free deep-loop-runtime backend. @context owns one-shot retrieval while research and review carry bounded context snapshots. Per-mode convergence, state, artifacts, and tool-permission contracts are preserved unflattened; the three-tier discriminator (workflowMode / runtimeLoopType / backendKind) keeps graph-backed modes and improvement-host/external-adapter modes distinct.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/09--council-graph-value-comparison/stalled-council-blocker-ranking-graph-vs-baseline.md:\n  Line 21: > **Automated test anchor:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-value-scenarios.vitest.ts` test name `DAC-030 graph beats no-graph baseline`. Measured baseline-vs-graph ratios live in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/council-graph-value-report.json`.\n\n  Line 103: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/query.cjs` | runtime CLI script |\n\n  Line 104: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/council-graph-query.ts` | `getConvergenceBlockers` helper |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-upsert-idempotency-and-self-loop-rejection.md:\n  Line 31: Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs`, which the scenario identifies as runtime CLI script: idempotent upsert + self-loop rejection. Validation is anchored by `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts`, covering test: \"upserts prompt-safe council graph data and queries unresolved disagreements and decision support\".\n\n  Line 43: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs` | Handler | runtime CLI script: idempotent upsert + self-loop rejection |\n\n  Line 44: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/council-graph-db.ts` | Library | Storage layer: unique constraints |\n\n  Line 45: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs` | Runtime CLI | Input validation and edge normalization |\n\n  Line 52: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` | Automated test | Test: \"upserts prompt-safe council graph data and queries unresolved disagreements and decision support\" |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/09--council-graph-value-comparison/convergence-safety-under-critical-disagreement-graph-vs-baseline.md:\n  Line 21: > **Automated test anchor:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-value-scenarios.vitest.ts` test name `DAC-029 graph beats no-graph baseline`. Measured baseline-vs-graph ratios live in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/council-graph-value-report.json`.\n\n  Line 102: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` | Three-state decision logic |\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"deep-loop-runtime|runtime/lib|runtime/scripts","time":{"start":1783486734604,"end":1783486734617}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f5cef82895da878016a4dd90e828c8191a474fd7a7cca5d6a"}},"id":"prt_f4017e105001x5vXqB7AqrgJkm","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","messageID":"msg_f4017b55c001pScbfYTroIoz79"}}
