s no per-mode logic. Each packet keeps its own convergence math, state shape, artifacts and tool-permission guards. The shared backend, `deep-loop-runtime`, does the executor configuration, prompt-pack rendering, validation, atomic state, coverage graph and scoring.\n\n  Line 61: - **`runtimeLoopType`** is the graph-backed convergence key for `deep-loop-runtime`, one of `research`, `review` or `council` for active modes. It is an explicit `null` for the four improvement lanes and is never guessed from `workflowMode`.\n\n  Line 92: | `deep-loop-runtime` | The frozen, MCP-free backend the modes run on. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/README.md:\n  Line 96: npx vitest run .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/tests/scorer.vitest.ts\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/README.md:\n  Line 41: It does not perform one-shot codebase lookup (`@context` does that), audit code (`deep-review`) or compare competing plans (`deep-ai-council`). The current deep-loop workflow roster has four active families: `deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-ai-council`, and `deep-improvement`; the improvement family includes four command lanes. The runtime-backed families share `deep-loop-runtime` for executors, state handling and coverage graphs, while improvement remains host-driven.\n\n  Line 65: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs <spec-folder>\n\n  Line 112: `deep-research` shares the `deep-loop-runtime` with the other active deep-loop families. Each owns a different phase and none crosses into another's territory.\n\n  Line 120: `/speckit:plan` and `/speckit:implement` consume the research report. `system-spec-kit` owns the spec folder, validation and memory continuity. `deep-loop-runtime` provides the shared executor, state layer and coverage graph.\n\n  Line 131: | Strategy or dashboard drift from iteration files | The reducer did not run after the last iteration write | Run `node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs <spec-folder>` to regenerate derived files |\n\n  Line 182: python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/validate_document.py .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/README.md --type readme\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md:\n  Line 41: It does not investigate outward knowledge (`deep-research`), perform one-shot codebase lookup (`@context`), compare competing plans (`deep-ai-council`) or run evaluator-first improvement lanes (`deep-improvement`). A single-pass review is `sk-code`'s code-review mode. The active deep-loop families share the `deep-loop-runtime` for executors, state handling and coverage graphs.\n\n  Line 67: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs <spec-folder>\n\n  Line 118: `deep-review` shares the `deep-loop-runtime` with the other active deep-loop families. Each owns a different phase and none crosses into another's territory.\n\n  Line 186: python3 .opencode/skills/sk-doc/scripts/validate_document.py .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md --type readme\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:\n  Line 101: npx vitest run .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/tests/scorer.vitest.ts\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/tests/README.md:\n  Line 20: cd .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts && npx vitest run model-benchmark/tests/\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/README.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Code-facing README for .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts.\"\n\n  Line 19: This README documents the code-bearing folder `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts` so operators can understand its role without opening every source file first. It follows the sk-doc skill README structure while staying focused on code navigation.\n\n  Line 39: Start with `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md` for runtime routing and workflow boundaries.\n\n  Line 44: rg --files .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts\n\n  Line 88: User request: Check .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts for sk-code and README coverage.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:\n  Line 148: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/generate-profile.cjs --agent=.opencode/agents/code.md\n\n  Line 154: npx vitest run --config .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/vitest.config.mjs\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/tests/fixtures/blocked-stop-session/README.md:\n  Line 25: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs \\\n\n  Line 26:   .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/tests/fixtures/blocked-stop-session\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/benchmark/README.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"deep-loop-workflows Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\"\n\n  Line 3: description: \"Benchmark inputs and reports for deep-loop-workflows, scored by the deep-improvement Lane C harness against the hub's manual_testing_playbook.\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"deep-loop-workflows routing benchmark\"\n\n  Line 10: # deep-loop-workflows Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\n\n  Line 12: > Reports for benchmarking how well `deep-loop-workflows` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.\n\n  Line 18: The deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `deep-loop-workflows` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). Two trace modes score the same corpus:\n\n  Line 23: Note: the harness itself lives inside this hub (`deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/`), so `deep-loop-workflows` benchmarks itself with the same Lane C tooling every other hub uses; there is no special-casing.\n\n  Line 29: | Corpus | deep-loop-workflows `manual_testing_playbook` (20 scenarios across 5 categories) |\n\n  Line 45: node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs \\\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime","time":{"start":1783486760214,"end":1783486760278}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a860e5d3a550a28016a4dd9281810819185a77862a44dd258"}},"id":"prt_f4018451400102wBZtBqFfdyEm","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","messageID":"msg_f40181d47001oDMb0EM7oKnpnx"}}
