ency order is appropriate and should remain fixed.\",\"Python and TypeScript advisor constants both carry the old merged skill id.\",\"routing-registry-drift-guard hardcodes both registryPath and projection hash skill input.\",\"Agent mirrors and root README carry duplicate live old-path references.\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:25:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deltas/iter-004.jsonl\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":4,\"run\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research execution=single_iteration\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring decision and fanout retry seam\",\"findingsCount\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.34,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the zero-caller gap and identified a safer integration seam than putting model policy inside the generic pool primitive.\",\"keyFindings\":[\"fallback-router.ts already supports typed failure routing and separate-pool fallback decisions.\",\"fanout-pool.cjs currently only schedules same-item retries until maxRetries, then fails the item.\",\"If phase 004 runs, fanout-run should own the model registry and pass fallback behavior into the pool rather than hardcoding model policy in the generic pool.\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:30:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deltas/iter-005.jsonl\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":5,\"run\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research execution=single_iteration\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Final stress test, verification ordering, and residual risks\",\"findingsCount\":2,\"newInfoRatio\":0.12,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Final pass mostly consolidated prior findings; only minor sequencing risks remained after all key questions had evidence-backed answers.\",\"keyFindings\":[\"Closeout must not claim success until runtime tests, system-spec-kit council tests, advisor rebaseline, mirror sync, and residual grep pass.\",\"Temporary compatibility symlinks are useful only during migration and must be gone before parent success criteria are evaluated.\"],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.3267,\"madNoiseFloor\":0.4448,\"entropyCoverage\":1.0,\"compositeStop\":0.7},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:35:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-config.json\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-state.jsonl\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deltas/iter-003.jsonl\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deltas/iter-004.jsonl\nA .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deltas/iter-005.jsonl","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/syst