{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783487287238,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","part":{"id":"prt_f40204fc4001l9fYdv9pZeRfzy","messageID":"msg_f40204ba6001BgXtQaS02b9079","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","snapshot":"94002b70425fb70be78ce5289c201128c497aa36","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487300323,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hAc2qkcOPK0hSpZB5W7GlMui","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy: gpt55-fast-4\n2: \n3: ## Scope\n4: \n5: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`.\n6: \n7: ## Execution Contract\n8: \n9: - Lineage: `gpt55-fast-4`\n10: - Session: `fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01`\n11: - Executor: `cli-opencode` using `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n12: - Artifact directory: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4`\n13: - Artifact root handling: bound directly to `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not used.\n14: - Stop policy: run at least 3 iterations, continue until legal convergence or max 10 iterations.\n15: \n16: ## Key Questions\n17: \n18: 1. Is the proposed `system-deep-loop` layout sound, especially keeping `runtime/` as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n19: 2. Does the bidirectional path-repair plan cover live internal coupling between runtime and workflow scripts?\n20: 3. Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow correctly scoped as path repair rather than dependency decoupling?\n21: 4. Does the external reference migration plan cover commands, agents, plugin/hook surfaces, READMEs, graph metadata, and advisor corpus safely?\n22: 5. Should `fallback-router.ts` wiring be part of the required merge, and where should it attach if implemented?\n23: \n24: ## Answered Questions\n25: \n26: 1. The target layout is sound if `runtime/` remains nested infrastructure and does not become a `mode-registry` workflow mode.\n27: 2. The path-repair table is mostly sound but should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to the internal repair scope.\n28: 3. Runtime package dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling and shared test discovery still borrow `system-spec-kit` paths; repairing those paths is necessary and sufficient for the structural merge.\n29: 4. The external migration order is sound because it updates hard constants before generated projections, compiled contracts, corpus/prose, graph metadata, and validation gates.\n30: 5. `fallback-router.ts` wiring should remain optional for the structural merge. If implemented, model fallback policy belongs in `fanout-run.cjs`, with the generic pool exposing or receiving a retry-exhausted substitution seam.\n31: \n32: ## What Worked\n33: \n34: - Reading the parent and child specs before live code kept the research aligned with the intended phase boundaries.\n35: - Splitting passes by risk area exposed the missing `replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` internal path and the advisor duplicated identity constants.\n36: - Comparing `fanout-pool.cjs` with `fanout-run.cjs` separated generic retry infrastructure from model-aware fanout policy.\n37: \n38: ## What Failed\n39: \n40: - Treating child 002's named internal path table as exhaustive missed one live deep-ai-council script.\n41: - Broad phrasing that the runtime is dependency-self-contained needs qualification: runtime dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling remains borrowed from `system-spec-kit`.\n42: - This lineage did not recompute the complete old-reference hit count; Stage A of child 003 still owns the authoritative baseline inventory.\n43: \n44: ## Exhausted Approaches\n45: \n46: - Adding `runtime/` as a workflow mode was rejected because the target architecture requires runtime to be infrastructure.\n47: - Fully decoupling TypeScript tooling during the structural move was rejected because it would blur merge validation with dependency/tooling cleanup.\n48: - Blind old-id replacement across the repo was rejected because advisor corpus and divergence ledgers require field-scoped edits and accuracy rebaseline.\n49: \n50: ## Ruled-Out Directions\n51: \n52: - Leaving compatibility symlinks through final completion.\n53: - Hardcoding GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro routing inside `fanout-pool.cjs`.\n54: - Treating fallback-router wiring as a blocker for the hub rename and runtime nesting.\n55: \n56: ## Next Focus\n57: \n58: Feed the correction set into fanout-level synthesis:\n59: \n60: 1. Add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to child 002 Stage 3a internal path repair.\n61: 2. Clarify child 004 so fallback model policy is owned by `fanout-run.cjs`, not hardcoded into generic pool code.\n62: 3. Preserve child 003 advisor drift, generated projection, corpus accuracy, mirror sync, and residual grep gates.\n\n(End of file - total 62 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy: gpt55-fast-4\n\n## Scope\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`.\n\n## Execution Contract\n\n- Lineage: `gpt55-fast-4`\n- Session: `fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01`\n- Executor: `cli-opencode` using `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n- Artifact directory: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4`\n- Artifact root handling: bound directly to `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not used.\n- Stop policy: run at least 3 iterations, continue until legal convergence or max 10 iterations.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n1. Is the proposed `system-deep-loop` layout sound, especially keeping `runtime/` as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n2. Does the bidirectional path-repair plan cover live internal coupling between runtime and workflow scripts?\n3. Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow correctly scoped as path repair rather than dependency decoupling?","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy: gpt55-fast-4\n\n## Scope\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`.\n\n## Execution Contract\n\n- Lineage: `gpt55-fast-4`\n- Session: `fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01`\n- Executor: `cli-opencode` using `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n- Artifact directory: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4`\n- Artifact root handling: bound directly to `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not used.\n- Stop policy: run at least 3 iterations, continue until legal convergence or max 10 iterations.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n1. Is the proposed `system-deep-loop` layout sound, especially keeping `runtime/` as infrastructure rather than a workflow mode?\n2. Does the bidirectional path-repair plan cover live internal coupling between runtime and workflow scripts?\n3. Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow correctly scoped as path repair rather than dependency decoupling?\n4. Does the external reference migration plan cover commands, agents, plugin/hook surfaces, READMEs, graph metadata, and advisor corpus safely?\n5. Should `fallback-router.ts` wiring be part of the required merge, and where should it attach if implemented?\n\n## Answered Questions\n\n1. The target layout is sound if `runtime/` remains nested infrastructure and does not become a `mode-registry` workflow mode.\n2. The path-repair table is mostly sound but should add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to the internal repair scope.\n3. Runtime package dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling and shared test discovery still borrow `system-spec-kit` paths; repairing those paths is necessary and sufficient for the structural merge.\n4. The external migration order is sound because it updates hard constants before generated projections, compiled contracts, corpus/prose, graph metadata, and validation gates.\n5. `fallback-router.ts` wiring should remain optional for the structural merge. If implemented, model fallback policy belongs in `fanout-run.cjs`, with the generic pool exposing or receiving a retry-exhausted substitution seam.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Reading the parent and child specs before live code kept the research aligned with the intended phase boundaries.\n- Splitting passes by risk area exposed the missing `replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` internal path and the advisor duplicated identity constants.\n- Comparing `fanout-pool.cjs` with `fanout-run.cjs` separated generic retry infrastructure from model-aware fanout policy.\n\n## What Failed\n\n- Treating child 002's named internal path table as exhaustive missed one live deep-ai-council script.\n- Broad phrasing that the runtime is dependency-self-contained needs qualification: runtime dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling remains borrowed from `system-spec-kit`.\n- This lineage did not recompute the complete old-reference hit count; Stage A of child 003 still owns the authoritative baseline inventory.\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n- Adding `runtime/` as a workflow mode was rejected because the target architecture requires runtime to be infrastructure.\n- Fully decoupling TypeScript tooling during the structural move was rejected because it would blur merge validation with dependency/tooling cleanup.\n- Blind old-id replacement across the repo was rejected because advisor corpus and divergence ledgers require field-scoped edits and accuracy rebaseline.\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- Leaving compatibility symlinks through final completion.\n- Hardcoding GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro routing inside `fanout-pool.cjs`.\n- Treating fallback-router wiring as a blocker for the hub rename and runtime nesting.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nFeed the correction set into fanout-level synthesis:\n\n1. Add `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to child 002 Stage 3a internal path repair.\n2. Clarify child 004 so fallback model policy is owned by `fanout-run.cjs`, not hardcoded into generic pool code.\n3. Preserve child 003 advisor drift, generated projection, corpus accuracy, mirror sync, and residual grep gates.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":62,"totalLines":62,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783487300253,"end":1783487300316}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09ad194582a527d3016a4ddb44284481919d08d0494214baf7"}},"id":"prt_f4020825b001rgqtqxnQki1Bzk","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","messageID":"msg_f40204ba6001BgXtQaS02b9079"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487300323,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_GqVV0qezMWcfEXRm8ASOHgGD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-findings-registry.json","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-findings-registry.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"schemaVersion\": \"deep-research-findings-registry.v1\",\n3:   \"lineage\": {\n4:     \"label\": \"gpt55-fast-4\",\n5:     \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01\",\n6:     \"generation\": 1,\n7:     \"executor\": {\n8:       \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\",\n9:       \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\"\n10:     }\n11:   },\n12:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n13:   \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n14:   \"iterations\": 5,\n15:   \"newInfoRatioTrend\": [0.92, 0.78, 0.52, 0.34, 0.12],\n16:   \"convergence\": {\n17:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.3267,\n18:     \"madNoiseFloor\": 0.4448,\n19:     \"entropyCoverage\": 1.0,\n20:     \"compositeStopScore\": 0.7,\n21:     \"legalStopGates\": \"pass\",\n22:     \"qualityGuards\": \"pass\"\n23:   },\n24:   \"findings\": [\n25:     {\n26:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F001\",\n27:       \"iteration\": 1,\n28:       \"category\": \"architecture\",\n29:       \"severity\": \"high\",\n30:       \"title\": \"Keep runtime nested as infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\n31:       \"claim\": \"The target system-deep-loop layout is sound only if runtime remains out of mode-registry and does not carry nested graph metadata as a workflow packet.\",\n32:       \"evidence\": [\n33:         \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:156\",\n34:         \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"\n35:       ],\n36:       \"recommendation\": \"Preserve runtime/ as an internal infrastructure subtree under system-deep-loop and keep workflow modes limited to deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, and deep-improvement.\",\n37:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n38:     },\n39:     {\n40:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F002\",\n41:       \"iteration\": 1,\n42:       \"category\": \"path-repair\",\n43:       \"severity\": \"medium\",\n44:       \"title\": \"Add replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs to internal path-repair scope\",\n45:       \"claim\": \"A live deep-ai-council script hardcodes old deep-loop-runtime script paths and should be repaired during child 002 internal path rewrites.\",\n46:       \"evidence\": [\n47:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26\",\n48:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:56\",\n49:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:65\"\n50:       ],\n51:       \"recommendation\": \"Patch child 002 Stage 3a or its implementation checklist to include this script alongside other internal workflow-to-runtime path repairs.\",\n52:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n53:     },\n54:     {\n55:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F003\",\n56:       \"iteration\": 2,\n57:       \"category\": \"tooling-coupling\",\n58:       \"severity\": \"medium\",\n59:       \"title\": \"Runtime dependency self-containment is partial\",\n60:       \"claim\": \"Runtime package dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling and type roots still borrow system-spec-kit paths.\",\n61:       \"evidence\": [\n62:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\",\n63:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:14\",\n64:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:20\",\n65:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12\"\n66:       ],\n67:       \"recommendation\": \"Keep the structural merge scoped to path-depth repair and avoid claiming full tooling decoupling until a separate cleanup packet owns it.\",\n68:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n69:     },\n70:     {\n71:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F004\",\n72:       \"iteration\": 2,\n73:       \"category\": \"test-discovery\",\n74:       \"severity\": \"medium\",\n75:       \"title\": \"system-spec-kit council test discovery must move to nested runtime paths\",\n76:       \"claim\": \"system-spec-kit still references runtime council tests through old relative paths and must be updated after nesting.\",\n77:       \"evidence\": [\n78:         \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\",\n79:         \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:20\"\n80:       ],\n81:       \"recommendation\": \"Repair the reverse test-discovery paths in the same structural phase as runtime nesting and keep system-spec-kit council tests in the closeout gate.\",\n82:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n83:     },\n84:     {\n85:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F005\",\n86:       \"iteration\": 3,\n87:       \"category\": \"advisor-migration\",\n88:       \"severity\": \"high\",\n89:       \"title\": \"Advisor merged-skill identity is duplicated across Python and TypeScript\",\n90:       \"claim\": \"The old deep-loop-workflows identity appears in advisor path constants and merged-id aliases, so migration must update both implementations and regenerate projections.\",\n91:       \"evidence\": [\n92:         \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\n93:         \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2579\",\n94:         \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\",\n95:         \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:26\",\n96:         \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:76\"\n97:       ],\n98:       \"recommendation\": \"Update Python, TypeScript, drift tests, generated projections, and corpus expectations as one advisor migration unit, followed by validation/rebaseline.\",\n99:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n100:     },\n101:     {\n102:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F006\",\n103:       \"iteration\": 3,\n104:       \"category\": \"agent-mirrors\",\n105:       \"severity\": \"medium\",\n106:       \"title\": \"OpenCode and Claude agent mirrors both carry old deep-loop paths\",\n107:       \"claim\": \"Mirrored agents need paired updates and mirror-sync validation after the skill identity and path migration.\",\n108:       \"evidence\": [\n109:         \".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\",\n110:         \".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\",\n111:         \".opencode/agents/ai-council.md:398\",\n112:         \".claude/agents/ai-council.md:380\"\n113:       ],\n114:       \"recommendation\": \"Treat agent mirrors as a synchronized migration surface and run the mirror-sync gate before closeout.\",\n115:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n116:     },\n117:     {\n118:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F007\",\n119:       \"iteration\": 4,\n120:       \"category\": \"fallback-routing\",\n121:       \"severity\": \"medium\",\n122:       \"title\": \"fallback-router.ts is tested but effectively unwired\",\n123:       \"claim\": \"The fallback router has typed routing and tests, but current fanout retry handling requeues the same item/model and records retry_exhausted after max retries without substitution.\",\n124:       \"evidence\": [\n125:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299\",\n126:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:422\",\n127:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:109\",\n128:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\n129:         \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"\n130:       ],\n131:       \"recommendation\": \"Keep fallback-router wiring optional for the structural merge; if child 004 proceeds, let fanout-run own model fallback policy and integrate through a retry-exhausted seam.\",\n132:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n133:     },\n134:     {\n135:       \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F008\",\n136:       \"iteration\": 5,\n137:       \"category\": \"verification\",\n138:       \"severity\": \"high\",\n139:       \"title\": \"Closeout must remove compatibility shims and pass full migration gates\",\n140:       \"claim\": \"Temporary compatibility paths are only acceptable during migration; parent success requires no old top-level skill folders and clean residual old-id grep outside allowlists.\",\n141:       \"evidence\": [\n142:         \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:100\",\n143:         \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:121\",\n144:         \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:129\"\n145:       ],\n146:       \"recommendation\": \"Block completion on runtime tests, system-spec-kit council tests, advisor rebaseline, divergence ratchet, mirror sync, residual grep, and deletion of temporary symlinks/shims.\",\n147:       \"confidence\": \"high\"\n148:     }\n149:   ]\n150: }\n\n(End of file - total 150 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"schemaVersion\": \"deep-research-findings-registry.v1\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"label\": \"gpt55-fast-4\",\n    \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"executor\": {\n      \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n  \"iterations\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatioTrend\": [0.92, 0.78, 0.52, 0.34, 0.12],\n  \"convergence\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.3267,\n    \"madNoiseFloor\": 0.4448,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 1.0,\n    \"compositeStopScore\": 0.7,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"schemaVersion\": \"deep-research-findings-registry.v1\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"label\": \"gpt55-fast-4\",\n    \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"executor\": {\n      \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\",\n      \"model\": \"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"stopReason\": \"converged\",\n  \"iterations\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatioTrend\": [0.92, 0.78, 0.52, 0.34, 0.12],\n  \"convergence\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.3267,\n    \"madNoiseFloor\": 0.4448,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 1.0,\n    \"compositeStopScore\": 0.7,\n    \"legalStopGates\": \"pass\",\n    \"qualityGuards\": \"pass\"\n  },\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F001\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"category\": \"architecture\",\n      \"severity\": \"high\",\n      \"title\": \"Keep runtime nested as infrastructure, not a workflow mode\",\n      \"claim\": \"The target system-deep-loop layout is sound only if runtime remains out of mode-registry and does not carry nested graph metadata as a workflow packet.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:156\",\n        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Preserve runtime/ as an internal infrastructure subtree under system-deep-loop and keep workflow modes limited to deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, and deep-improvement.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F002\",\n      \"iteration\": 1,\n      \"category\": \"path-repair\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"title\": \"Add replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs to internal path-repair scope\",\n      \"claim\": \"A live deep-ai-council script hardcodes old deep-loop-runtime script paths and should be repaired during child 002 internal path rewrites.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:56\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:65\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Patch child 002 Stage 3a or its implementation checklist to include this script alongside other internal workflow-to-runtime path repairs.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F003\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"tooling-coupling\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"title\": \"Runtime dependency self-containment is partial\",\n      \"claim\": \"Runtime package dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling and type roots still borrow system-spec-kit paths.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:14\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:20\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Keep the structural merge scoped to path-depth repair and avoid claiming full tooling decoupling until a separate cleanup packet owns it.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F004\",\n      \"iteration\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"test-discovery\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"title\": \"system-spec-kit council test discovery must move to nested runtime paths\",\n      \"claim\": \"system-spec-kit still references runtime council tests through old relative paths and must be updated after nesting.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json:31\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:20\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Repair the reverse test-discovery paths in the same structural phase as runtime nesting and keep system-spec-kit council tests in the closeout gate.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F005\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"category\": \"advisor-migration\",\n      \"severity\": \"high\",\n      \"title\": \"Advisor merged-skill identity is duplicated across Python and TypeScript\",\n      \"claim\": \"The old deep-loop-workflows identity appears in advisor path constants and merged-id aliases, so migration must update both implementations and regenerate projections.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2579\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:26\",\n        \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts:76\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Update Python, TypeScript, drift tests, generated projections, and corpus expectations as one advisor migration unit, followed by validation/rebaseline.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F006\",\n      \"iteration\": 3,\n      \"category\": \"agent-mirrors\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"title\": \"OpenCode and Claude agent mirrors both carry old deep-loop paths\",\n      \"claim\": \"Mirrored agents need paired updates and mirror-sync validation after the skill identity and path migration.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\",\n        \".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\",\n        \".opencode/agents/ai-council.md:398\",\n        \".claude/agents/ai-council.md:380\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Treat agent mirrors as a synchronized migration surface and run the mirror-sync gate before closeout.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F007\",\n      \"iteration\": 4,\n      \"category\": \"fallback-routing\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"title\": \"fallback-router.ts is tested but effectively unwired\",\n      \"claim\": \"The fallback router has typed routing and tests, but current fanout retry handling requeues the same item/model and records retry_exhausted after max retries without substitution.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:422\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:109\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\n        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Keep fallback-router wiring optional for the structural merge; if child 004 proceeds, let fanout-run own model fallback policy and integrate through a retry-exhausted seam.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt55-fast-4-F008\",\n      \"iteration\": 5,\n      \"category\": \"verification\",\n      \"severity\": \"high\",\n      \"title\": \"Closeout must remove compatibility shims and pass full migration gates\",\n      \"claim\": \"Temporary compatibility paths are only acceptable during migration; parent success requires no old top-level skill folders and clean residual old-id grep outside allowlists.\",\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:100\",\n        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:121\",\n        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:129\"\n      ],\n      \"recommendation\": \"Block completion on runtime tests, system-spec-kit council tests, advisor rebaseline, divergence ratchet, mirror sync, residual grep, and deletion of temporary symlinks/shims.\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\"\n    }\n  ]\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":150,"totalLines":150,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1783487300272,"end":1783487300320}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09ad194582a527d3016a4ddb44284c8191a02f6b724fd6ca1c"}},"id":"prt_f4020829f001tps29nRWLYQEYV","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","messageID":"msg_f40204ba6001BgXtQaS02b9079"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487300323,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vO66oVDTpRsjvOVmBBIZpNL0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Dashboard: gpt55-fast-4\n2: \n3: ## Status\n4: \n5: - State: complete\n6: - Stop reason: converged\n7: - Iterations: 5 of max 10\n8: - Session: `fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01`\n9: - Executor: `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n10: \n11: ## Convergence\n12: \n13: | Metric | Value |\n14: | --- | ---: |\n15: | newInfoRatio trend | 0.92, 0.78, 0.52, 0.34, 0.12 |\n16: | rolling average | 0.3267 |\n17: | MAD noise floor | 0.4448 |\n18: | entropy coverage | 1.0 |\n19: | composite stop score | 0.70 |\n20: | legal stop gates | pass |\n21: | quality guards | pass |\n22: \n23: ## Iteration Summary\n24: \n25: | Iteration | Focus | Findings | newInfoRatio | Result |\n26: | ---: | --- | ---: | ---: | --- |\n27: | 1 | Structural layout and identity boundaries | 4 | 0.92 | Missing internal path-repair script identified |\n28: | 2 | system-spec-kit tooling-borrow and runtime boundary | 4 | 0.78 | Tooling borrow confirmed and scoped |\n29: | 3 | External reference migration and advisor corpus | 4 | 0.52 | Advisor and mirror migration surfaces confirmed |\n30: | 4 | Fallback-router wiring decision | 3 | 0.34 | Optional wiring seam clarified |\n31: | 5 | Final stress test and verification ordering | 2 | 0.12 | Convergence reached |\n32: \n33: ## High-Impact Findings\n34: \n35: 1. `runtime/` should remain nested infrastructure, not a `mode-registry` workflow mode.\n36: 2. `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` should be added to child 002 internal path repair.\n37: 3. Runtime package dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling still borrows `system-spec-kit` paths.\n38: 4. Advisor migration must update Python, TypeScript, drift tests, generated projections, and corpus expectations together.\n39: 5. Fallback-router wiring is not a structural merge blocker; if implemented, policy should live in `fanout-run.cjs`.\n40: 6. Completion must be blocked on symlink/shim removal plus runtime, council, advisor, mirror, and residual grep gates.\n41: \n42: ## Risk Table\n43: \n44: | Risk | Level | Mitigation |\n45: | --- | --- | --- |\n46: | Missing one internal old-runtime path after nesting | Medium | Add `replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to child 002 Stage 3a |\n47: | Advisor old identity remains in one implementation | High | Update Python + TypeScript + drift test + generated projections as one unit |\n48: | Runtime self-containment overclaimed | Medium | Phrase as local runtime dependencies with remaining tooling borrow |\n49: | Blind replacement corrupts advisor corpus semantics | High | Use field-scoped corpus edits and rebaseline accuracy |\n50: | Fallback policy hardcoded into generic pool | Medium | Keep model policy in `fanout-run.cjs` and use a retry-exhausted seam |\n51: | Temporary compatibility shim left at completion | High | Block final completion on residual grep and removal of old top-level folders |\n52: \n53: ## Closeout Recommendation\n54: \n55: Proceed with parent fanout synthesis using this lineage as a confirming-plus-correction input. The only plan correction with direct implementation impact is the missing internal path-repair site in child 002. The fallback-router finding should inform child 004 wording but should not block the structural merge.\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Dashboard: gpt55-fast-4\n\n## Status\n\n- State: complete\n- Stop reason: converged\n- Iterations: 5 of max 10\n- Session: `fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01`\n- Executor: `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n\n## Convergence\n\n| Metric | Value |\n| --- | ---: |\n| newInfoRatio trend | 0.92, 0.78, 0.52, 0.34, 0.12 |\n| rolling average | 0.3267 |\n| MAD noise floor | 0.4448 |\n| entropy coverage | 1.0 |\n| composite stop score | 0.70 |\n| legal stop gates | pass |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-dashboard.md","text":"# Deep Research Dashboard: gpt55-fast-4\n\n## Status\n\n- State: complete\n- Stop reason: converged\n- Iterations: 5 of max 10\n- Session: `fanout-gpt55-fast-4-1783486518892-2qss01`\n- Executor: `cli-opencode` / `openai/gpt-5.5-fast`\n\n## Convergence\n\n| Metric | Value |\n| --- | ---: |\n| newInfoRatio trend | 0.92, 0.78, 0.52, 0.34, 0.12 |\n| rolling average | 0.3267 |\n| MAD noise floor | 0.4448 |\n| entropy coverage | 1.0 |\n| composite stop score | 0.70 |\n| legal stop gates | pass |\n| quality guards | pass |\n\n## Iteration Summary\n\n| Iteration | Focus | Findings | newInfoRatio | Result |\n| ---: | --- | ---: | ---: | --- |\n| 1 | Structural layout and identity boundaries | 4 | 0.92 | Missing internal path-repair script identified |\n| 2 | system-spec-kit tooling-borrow and runtime boundary | 4 | 0.78 | Tooling borrow confirmed and scoped |\n| 3 | External reference migration and advisor corpus | 4 | 0.52 | Advisor and mirror migration surfaces confirmed |\n| 4 | Fallback-router wiring decision | 3 | 0.34 | Optional wiring seam clarified |\n| 5 | Final stress test and verification ordering | 2 | 0.12 | Convergence reached |\n\n## High-Impact Findings\n\n1. `runtime/` should remain nested infrastructure, not a `mode-registry` workflow mode.\n2. `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` should be added to child 002 internal path repair.\n3. Runtime package dependencies are local, but TypeScript tooling still borrows `system-spec-kit` paths.\n4. Advisor migration must update Python, TypeScript, drift tests, generated projections, and corpus expectations together.\n5. Fallback-router wiring is not a structural merge blocker; if implemented, policy should live in `fanout-run.cjs`.\n6. Completion must be blocked on symlink/shim removal plus runtime, council, advisor, mirror, and residual grep gates.\n\n## Risk Table\n\n| Risk | Level | Mitigation |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Missing one internal old-runtime path after nesting | Medium | Add `replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` to child 002 Stage 3a |\n| Advisor old identity remains in one implementation | High | Update Python + TypeScript + drift test + generated projections as one unit |\n| Runtime self-containment overclaimed | Medium | Phrase as local runtime dependencies with remaining tooling borrow |\n| Blind replacement corrupts advisor corpus semantics | High | Use field-scoped corpus edits and rebaseline accuracy |\n| Fallback policy hardcoded into generic pool | Medium | Keep model policy in `fanout-run.cjs` and use a retry-exhausted seam |\n| Temporary compatibility shim left at completion | High | Block final completion on residual grep and removal of old top-level folders |\n\n## Closeout Recommendation\n\nProceed with parent fanout synthesis using this lineage as a confirming-plus-correction input. The only plan correction with direct implementation impact is the missing internal path-repair site in child 002. The fallback-router finding should inform child 004 wording but should not block the structural merge.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":55,"totalLines":55,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-4/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1783487300285,"end":1783487300322}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09ad194582a527d3016a4ddb4428508191aec039bd59447699"}},"id":"prt_f402082b300175IDokwy6d7Ocl","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66afffetpkX52bffjbY3h","messageID":"msg_f40204ba6001BgXtQaS02b9079"}}
